SUMMARY: Wall To Wall Soul: Photographic Tribute to Portland's Historic B
 lack Musician Community
DESCRIPTION:Feb 1 - Mar 31\, 2026\n\nWall To Wall Soul pays tribute to Po
 rtland's historic Black musician community\, rooted in the Albina Distric
 t during the mid-20th century. The exhibit provides access to archival ph
 otography from the Albina Community Archive https://www.albinacommunityar
 chive.org/ —much of which has been restored\, recolored\, and in some cas
 es reconstructed from source materials. Photography featured in the show 
 was selected from roughly 180 private collections in the care of Albina M
 usic Trust.\n\nVisitors can check out the Wall To Wall Soul pop-up at The
  Old Church Concert Hall from February 2nd-March 27th\, 2026. Below you c
 an learn more about the musicians featured in the framed portraits seen a
 t the venue.\n\nExhibition on display at The Old Church\, courtesy of Alb
 ina Music Trust\, Feb 1 - Mar 31 2026\n\nFree during office hours https:/
 /www.tocportland.org/visit Tuesday-Friday 11 AM - 3 PM. Please use the 11
 th Ave Entrance and ring intercom for access.\n\nAlso on view during even
 ing events https://www.tocportland.org/upcoming-shows with event admissio
 n.
CATEGORIES:lunchtime-concerts
