SUMMARY: Black Mystery Month | Roman Norfleet & Be Present Art Group
DESCRIPTION:Doors at 6:30pm | All Ages | Bar w/ ID | Tickets GA $22\n\nTh
 e 3rd Annual Black Mystery Month Concert\nfeaturing:\n\n\n"Out Of The Inf
 inite Darkness"\nA sono-drama performed by:\nRoman Norfleet & Be Present 
 Art Group\n\n\nOpening Performances by:\nWoseiko Ensemble\nJacque Hammond
 \n\n\nFashion Market by:\nAmen\, Amen Studio\n\n\nPresented by Albina Mus
 ic Trust & KMHD\n\n\n“Out of the Infinite Darkness” is a cosmic sono-dram
 a performed by Roman Norfleet & Be Present Art Group\, featuring an 8-pie
 ce ensemble with dancers. Interpreted through sound and movement\, and dr
 awing on Afro-diasporic imagination and imagery\, the work imagines life 
 before the humanoid form—spirit and energy-beings emerging from the infin
 ite darkness of space and descending to Earth.\n\n\nThe piece explores da
 rkness not as a racial construct\, but as an original\, generative force 
 that predates “blackness\,” melanin\, and physical form itself. Through l
 ayered sonic storytelling\, these beings take on human bodies\, reckon wi
 th new physical experience\, navigate chaos and evolution\, discover spir
 itual mission and purpose\, and ultimately transition into another realm—
 into ancestorhood. Written by Roman Norfleet.
