SUMMARY: Lunchtime Concert: Golden West Brass
DESCRIPTION:TOC presents Lunchtime FREE Concerts every FIRST and THIRD We
 dnesday of the month. Our gift to the community for over 56 years\, join 
 us in person or on our Youtube Channel. https://www.youtube.com/channel/U
 CLiO4ZclyOFIe8HiOFzWJyg\n\nThe brass quintet\, Golden West Brass\, is the
  traveling branch of musicians from the larger Air Force Band of the Gold
 en West based in Travis Air Force Base\, California. Their goal is to har
 ness musical excellence to honor those who have served\, and to connect t
 he Air Force with the general public and community partners. Using world-
 class musical performances\, Golden West Brass uses music to bridge cultu
 ral\, linguistic\, and socioeconomic differences to advance international
  relationships and inspire positive experiences for all.\n\nThey will be 
 performing music from Shostakovich\, Fats Waller\, Defying Gravity from W
 icked\, and a patriotic medley.\n\nBorn out of a nation about to enter th
 e Second World War\, the United States Air Force Band started as one of 5
 9 “Air Force Bands” activated on October 1\, 1941. The Band’s unsurpassed
  professionalism and proximity to the Headquarters for the Army Air Force
 s on Bolling Field in Washington\, D.C. quickly earned it the designation
  as “The Official Band of the Army Air Forces.” The Band’s name officiall
 y changed to the United States Air Force Band with creation of the the U.
 S. Air Force in 1947.\n\nTo learn more: https://www.music.af.mil/Bands/US
 -Air-Force-Band-of-the-Golden-West/ www.music.af.mil/Bands/US-Air-Force-B
 and-of-the-Golden-West/ http://www.music.af.mil/Bands/US-Air-Force-Band-o
 f-the-Golden-West/\n\nWATCH THE LIVESTREAM https://youtube.com/live/f91bI
 QPBUdQ\n\n
CATEGORIES:lunchtime-concerts
