SUMMARY: Biamp Portland Jazz Festival: Charlie Brown III
DESCRIPTION:Doors at 7pm | All Ages | Bar w/ ID | Tickets $31.50 member /
  $36.50 adv / $41.50 dos\n\nA Portland native\, Charlie Brown III is a mu
 sical director\, producer\, and keyboardist whose work has gained interna
 tional renown in recent years. Brown has gained wider exposure when produ
 cing for mainstream rap artist\, Aminé\, and has spent ample time as a fi
 xture in the tight-knit live unit supporting Memphis-based bass guitar pr
 odigy\, MonoNeon. Pushing the boundaries of jazz and new music\, Brown do
 es so with a unique knack for both composition and improvisation both on 
 stage\, and in the studio. He currently splits time producing and perform
 ing with his group Greaterkind in Portland\, as well as hitting the inter
 national touring circuit with a variety of acts. Brown is co-director of 
 the Brown Branch Big Band\, and also has music of his own he curates and 
 records.
