SUMMARY: TOC Presents: Omar Sosa & Seckou Keita Suba Trio feat. Gustavo O
 valles\, Percussion
DESCRIPTION:Doors 6:30pm | All Ages | Bar w/ ID | ADV Premium Seating $35
  / DOS Premium Seating $40 / ADV GA $30 / DOS GA $35\n*Pricing Includes a
 ll ticketing fees*\n\nSUBA Trio unites 7-time GRAMMY-nominated composer a
 nd pianist Omar Sosa\, Senegalese kora master and singer Seckou Keita\, a
 nd Afro-Venezuelan percussionist Gustavo Ovalles in a rich transatlantic 
 collaboration rooted in shared African ancestry. Blending jazz with Afro-
 Cuban and West African traditions\, their music feels both expansive and 
 deeply intimate.\n\nNamed one of NPR Music’s “20 Best Albums of 2021\,” S
 UBA has been praised for a sound that “moves like a serene sunset in the 
 Sahel desert” (Jazz Weekly). Their performance at The Old Church will fea
 ture music from the album alongside dynamic improvisations\, exploring th
 e joyful and spiritual connections at the heart of their shared musical r
 oots.
