SUMMARY: Classical Unbuttoned
DESCRIPTION:Doors at 6:30pm | All Ages | Bar w/ ID | Tickets ADV $25 / DO
 S $35 / Kids 12 & Under ADV $17 DOS $27\n\nJoin us for an evening with wo
 rld renowned Steinway Artist Julian Gargiulo\, in his much-anticipated de
 but at The Old Church in Portland.\n\n-Commonly referred to as the “Piani
 st with the Hair” because of his distinctive look\, Julian is an internat
 ionally recognized classical pianist\, composer\, and humorist who perfor
 ms all over the world\, -in prestigious venues from New York’s Carnegie H
 all to the Sydney Opera House - and has been featured on Radio and TV sta
 tions across North America\, Europe\, and Asia\, and most recently on BBC
  Radio 3 in London. His compositions have become viral internet sensation
 s\, amassing over 8 million streams on Amazon Music. His first recording 
 for Deutsche Grammophon with violinist María Dueñas was released to wide 
 acclaim last year.\n\n“Saturday Night Live meets Carnegie Hall” (Huffingt
 on Post)\n\n"He's the only classical musician I know who could truly be r
 egarded as a rock star as well." (The Courier Mail)\n\n"Expect to revise 
 any preconceived notions you have about classical music concerts." (Huffi
 ngton Post)\n\n“Makes Howard Stern look almost tame” (The New York Times)
 \n\nJulian invites his audience to abandon all preconceived notions about
  classical concerts and captivates crowds with both technical precision a
 nd personable wit.\n\n
