SUMMARY: Mt. Hood Jazz Festival presents Emmet Cohen Quintet
DESCRIPTION:Doors 6:00pm | All Ages | Bar w/ ID | Tickets $30 @ Ticket To
 mato https://mhcc.tickettomato.com/event/9841\n\nThe Mt. Hood Jazz Festiv
 al kicks off its five-day immersion into the jazz culture at The Old Chur
 ch! This first event includes professional performances by world-renowned
  artists.\n\nIn celebration of the centennial of John Coltrane and Miles 
 Davis\, pianist Emmet Cohen brings together an all-star quintet to explor
 e the fundamental questions that shaped their artistry: Why are we here? 
 What are we reaching for? Where does the music take us?\n\nJoining him ar
 e four of today’s leading voices\, including:\n\n  * Tivon Pennicott (sax
 ophone)\n  * Jeremy Pelt (trumpet)\n  * Yasushi Nakamura (bass)\n  * Joe 
 Farnsworth (drums)\n\nTogether\, this powerhouse ensemble reimagines the 
 spirit and sound of two of jazz’s most iconic innovators through improvis
 ational brilliance\, emotional depth\, and cultural resonance.\n\nWednesd
 ay\, April 22\n\n7:00 pm – Miles & Coltrane at 100 – $30\n\nTickets are N
 onrefundable. The Mt. Hood Jazz Festival will not be accepting donated-ba
 ck tickets in 2026.
