SUMMARY: The Moth StorySLAM: American Dreams
DESCRIPTION:The Moth StorySLAM is an open-mic storytelling competition in
  which anyone can share a true\, personal\, 5-minute story on the night's
  theme. Sign up for a chance to tell a story or sit back and enjoy the sh
 ow! Tonight’s theme is…\n\nAMERICAN DREAMS: Tell us a five-minute story a
 bout your lifelong aspiration. Pulling off the impossible or failing in s
 pectacular fashion. Overcoming the odds\, shirking expectations\, forging
  your own path\, come hell or high water. Give us your big swings\, your 
 wildest flights of fancy\, your most epic home runs or your dreams dashed
  and deferred. Does the American Dream still exist? You tell us.\n\nDoors
  Open: 7:00 PM\n\nShow Starts: 8:00 PM\n\nTickets for Portland's StorySLA
 Ms go on sale 3 weeks prior to the show date at 3 PM ET.\n\nSeating is no
 t guaranteed and is available on a first-come\, first-served basis. Pleas
 e be sure to arrive at least 10 minutes before the show. Admission is not
  guaranteed for late arrivals. All sales final. As many as 10 tickets may
  be available at the door for all of our StorySLAMs on a first-come\, fir
 st-served basis.\n\nThis venue is 16+
